  "texts": [
    "These synthetic images are particularly valuable for training on rare diseases and hard-to-diagnose conditions, addressing the challenge of limited data availability [93].",
    "Additionally, synthetic datasets ensure patient privacy while offering realistic training material, improving diagnostic accuracy and comprehension of orthopedic imaging.",
    "Generative adversarial networks (GANs) and their variants also play a critical role in medical imaging applications [94].",
    "used StyleGAN2-ADA to generate knee X-ray images that accurately depicted stages of arthritis progression, enabling trainees to study disease characteristics in a controlled, customizable manner [95].",
    "MedGAN is an adaptive GAN that addresses challenges like model collapse and convergence issues associated with traditional GANs [96]."
  ],
